description: Deletes a snapshot of a volume. You can take snapshots of your gateway volumes on a scheduled or ad hoc basis. This API action enables you to delete a snapshot schedule for a volume. For more information, see Backing up your volumes. In the DeleteSnapshotSchedule request, you identify the volume by providing its Amazon Resource Name (ARN). This operation is only supported for cached volume gateway types.

parameters.name: VolumeARN
parameters.description: The volume which snapshot schedule to delete.

nested_items.name: VolumeARN
nested_items.description: The volume which snapshot schedule was deleted.
